name: WINDPROOF AND WATERPROOF RECCO¬Æ TECHNOLOGY DOWN JACKET SKI COLLECTION
description:
Down puffer jacket made with 85% down and 15% feather fill with 750 fill power for heat insulation, allowing for thermal comfort practicing snowboard/ski activities in temperatures down to -18¬∫C (-0.4¬∫F). Fabric is double-layered wind- and waterproof with up to a 15,000 mm water column and combines an exterior shell with an interior membrane that prevents water penetration but allows air through, providing breathability. Heat-sealed seams that reinforce protection against snow and rain. Equipped with RECCO¬Æ* technology to help rescue professionals find you in case of an accident, avalanche, or getting lost in difficult-to-reach areas.

High collar with polar fleece lining and hood. Long sleeves with elasticized cuffs. Sleeve pocket for lift ticket. Adjustable ventilation at underarms with hidden in-seam zip closure.

Interior pocket for cell phone. Front pockets with polar fleece interior lining and zip closure. Interior mesh pocket for gloves with glasses cleaner. 

Removable interior tail to keep out snow and adjustable hem with elastic straps to prevent cold from getting in. Front waterproof double runner zipper closure with adjustable ventilation panel. Seamless padding designed to reduce the amount of topstitching and avoid the entrance of wind and water. 

*For more information about RECCO¬Æ technology, please visit their website: https://recco.com
